    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "therapists and crisis lines feel so performative though. it's just more people trying to fix a problem that isn't really a problem, it's just the reality of my life. i'm just a tiny speck in a huge city where nobody knows my name. if i just drifted away, it wouldn't be a tragedy, it would just be... quiet. doesn't that sound kind of better than fighting to be \"seen\" all the time?",
